video fellow
the buzzfeed video fellowship is a three-month program for the next generation of video producer eager to master the tool and technique of the social web over the course of the program you will learn how to create compelling shareable short-form video content this includes developing production skill from conception to execution - brainstorming writing producing shooting editing post-production note -- and exploring how and why people view and share video through buzzfeed youtube snapchat facebook twitter pinterest and other social site
you are a native of the digital and pop culture landscape with intimate knowledge of the latest and greatest in emerging technology platform you are obsessed with cultural meme propagation and devour the thing people are sharing liking recommending and talking about
fellows will work with and learn from member of the buzzfeed video team this is the perfect fellowship for someone interested in pursuing a career in entertainment new medium or creative service who is fascinated by the web social network human psychology pop culture and the changing medium landscape
this is a full-time paid three-month fellowship based in los angeles
responsibilities
develop mastery of established buzzfeed video format style content generation method and production process
conceive write shoot edit and produce video buzzfeed
work with senior producer to discover and create new recurring video format to live on buzzfeed youtube and other video sharing service
requirements
1-2 year of proven experience creating compelling shareable video content
proficiency with dslr camera sound lighting equipment and editing suite
adobe creative suite and on set experience a plus
ability to work in small team and independently
ability to give and receive constructive criticism high emotional intelligence
a competitive drive
a positive curious and kind disposition no hater
